The paper focuses on improving feature representations for image classification, which is a core problem in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves postprocessing off-the-shelf feature representations, which is a technique commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions natural language processing (cs.CL) and speech recognition, but the majority of the content is focused on image classification. Finally, the paper evaluates the proposed method on various datasets, which is a common practice in multimedia (cs.MM) research.
